==Prize money dispute==
In January 2016, several clubs threatened to withdraw from the competition due a disagreement regarding prize money. CONMEBOL had offered a 40% increase on what was given in the 2015 edition but clubs wanted a 150% increase.<ref>{{cite web|last=Panja|first=Tariq|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-01-26/clubs-threaten-to-walk-out-of-top-soccer-event-in-cash-dispute|title=Clubs Threaten to Walk Out of Top Soccer Event in Cash Dispute|work=Bloomberg|date=26 January 2016}}</ref> On 2 February, CONMEBOL announced that the prize money paid to each club was doubled from the previous amount.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/02022016-2359/conmebol-duplica-ingresos-para-clubes-en-la-copa-bridgestone-libertadores|title=CONMEBOL duplica ingresos para clubes en la Copa Bridgestone Libertadores|publisher=CONMEBOL.com|date=2 February 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>

